Bonus Interview Question
Interviewer: Tell me about a challenging Azure DevOps issue you resolved.

Sample Answer (based on your experience):

One challenging issue involved Azure Artifacts where upstream package versions, such as Microsoft.AspNetCore.App.Ref, were not visible across multiple feeds, even before any package deletion. I first verified the upstream source configuration and feed permissions, then compared behavior across feeds to rule out feed-specific issues. I checked Azure DevOps service health, validated that the package was part of the .NET shared framework rather than a typical NuGet package, and reviewed feed settings and caching behavior. Since the issue was reproducible across multiple feeds, I gathered logs and evidence, documented the troubleshooting steps, and escalated the issue to Microsoft Support with all relevant details. This systematic approach helped narrow the problem to a platform-level behavior rather than a configuration issue and minimized unnecessary changes to the environment.
